    <link>https://leakfree.org/t/pixelated-skyboxes-with-fix/10470</link>
    <description>Ok, this may sound like nitpicking, but it&#39;s so easy to fix that I decided to report it.
Under close inspection, the HDR skyboxes look very pixelated, thanks to a bug within the Source Engine.
![](upload://sBwBpglUGFXH48sw8ecVna0uJ9W.jpeg)
[b]Fixing:[/b]
![](upload://jzSYSlj4yei53mv4RHb1x88ds3Y.png)
Just check the &quot;Point Sample&quot; flag and save the file. It seems that the engine belives it&#39;s &quot;true&quot; when it&#39;s &quot;false&quot; and vice-versa.
Fixed sky:
![](upload://1iVZsnOFADoIK1Ae2fPQVHeLQy4.jpeg)
Also feel free to check [url=https://spockjedi.webs.com/HDR%20TUTORIAL.html]my article.[/url] There are some tips on how to properly compile HDR skyboxes there.
And congratulations for the awesome mod! I can&#39;t wait to play Xen.  :smiley:</description>
    
